One person has been killed and two children slightly injured following a collision between two bakkies on the N1 in Matjiesfontein in the Karoo. Western Cape Traffic Chief Kenny Africa says the driver of one of the vehicle failed to stop at a crossing, leading to the crash. Occupants in the other vehicle were not injured. “There was a collision between a Volkswagen Amarok and a Toyota Double Cab LDV. In this accident, the driver of the Toyota double Cab got killed and two of his passengers, both kids, were slightly injured. Luckily the occupants in the Amarok were not injured.”  About Corbin August View all posts by Corbin August